# Epic 4: Advanced Iframe Interaction & User Personalization

## Problem Analysis

- **Goal**: Implement a highly interactive and customizable user dashboard experience, including user-selectable menu positions, advanced iframe state management, clear visual indicators in menus, and specific interaction behaviors.
- **Key Requirements**:
  - Implement persistent user settings for layout and theme
  - Create robust iframe state management system
  - Build desktop "Top Menu" navigation experience
  - Implement desktop "Side Menu" navigation experience
  - Add click and long-press interactions for URLs
  - Ensure mobile compatibility for all features

## Current Status

### 2025-05-27 23:10

**Status**: In Progress

- What's working: User settings persistence implemented with theme and menu position preferences
- What's not: Missing menu position layout implementations and iframe state management
- Blocking issues: None - Epic 1-3 functionality is assumed to be in place
- Next actions: full testing for Story 4.1
- Documentation updates needed:
  - [x] User settings documentation
  - [ ] Iframe state management documentation
  - [ ] Navigation and interaction documentation

## Implementation Steps

- [ ] **Story 4.1: Implement Persistent User Settings for Layout**
  - [x] Define UserSetting Prisma model with theme (Enum: `LIGHT`, `DARK`, `SYSTEM` default) and menuPosition (Enum: `TOP` default, `SIDE`)
  - [x] Update User model with one-to-one relation to UserSetting
  - [x] Create migration and apply to database
  - [x] Add logic to auto-create UserSetting records with defaults (`theme: SYSTEM`, `menuPosition: TOP`) whenever a new User is created
  - [x] Implement backend API endpoints:
    - [x] `GET /api/user/settings` to fetch the authenticated user's settings
    - [x] `PUT /api/user/settings` to update theme and/or menuPosition with validation
  - [x] Enhance NextAuth.js session data to include persisted theme and menuPosition preferences
  - [x] Create UI controls in User Settings page:
    - [x] "Layout & Appearance Preferences" section
    - [x] UI controls for menu position with static image previews
    - [x] UI controls for theme with themed preview boxes (selected has blue highlight)
    - [x] "Save Preferences" button that updates settings via API
  - [x] Add dynamic header adaptation based on preferences:
    - [x] Desktop: Three-section structure for "Top Menu" vs. hidden for "Side Menu"
    - [x] Mobile: Consistent header regardless of preference
  - [x] Implement dynamic dashboard layout based on preferences:
    - [x] "Top Menu" preference shows URL/Group navigation in AppBar's central area
    - [x] "Side Menu" preference shows persistent side panel for navigation
  - [x] Create theme application and toggle functionality:
    - [x] Use MUI ThemeProvider with persisted theme
    - [x] Support SYSTEM theme with OS preference detection (prefers-color-scheme)
    - [x] Fall back to DARK if OS preference undetectable
  - Success criteria: Users can personalize layout and theme with persistence
  - Dependencies: Epic 1 (User Schema), Epic 2 (User Profile)

- [ ] **Story 4.2: Implement Core Iframe State Management**
  - [ ] Create IframeProvider React Context:
    - [ ] Store managedIframes Map<string, { originalSrc: string; currentSrc: string; isLoaded: boolean; }>
    - [ ] Track activeUrlIdentifier
  - [ ] Implement useIframeManager custom hook with optimized methods:
    - [ ] getIframeData(id), isUrlLoaded(id)
    - [ ] setActiveUrl(id, srcForDataSrc)
    - [ ] markAsLoaded(id), markAsUnloaded(id)
    - [ ] triggerReload(id)
    - [ ] getAllManagedIframesForRender()
  - [ ] Add iframe rendering logic:
    - [ ] Iterate getAllManagedIframesForRender() to render iframes
    - [ ] Set src and data-src attributes appropriately
  - [ ] Implement CSS visibility control:
    - [ ] Active iframe: visibility: visible
    - [ ] Inactive iframes: visibility: hidden; position: absolute; left: -9999px;
  - [ ] Add iframe sandbox attributes for security:
    - [ ] sandbox="allow-scripts allow-same-origin allow-popups allow-forms allow-downloads allow-popups-to-escape-sandbox"
  - [ ] Create mechanisms for tracking loaded status:
    - [ ] Monitor onload (calls markAsLoaded)
    - [ ] Monitor onerror (status remains loaded: false)
    - [ ] Display UI error for active iframe load failures
  - [ ] Implement state preservation verification:
    - [ ] Test loading URL A, scrolling, loading URL B, then showing A again to verify state preservation
  - [ ] Add support for initial URL loading:
    - [ ] Integrate with Story 3.9's initial auto-load functionality
  - [ ] Optimize for performance using memoized React Context and React.memo for consumers
  - Success criteria: Robust iframe state management with visibility control
  - Dependencies: Story 3.9

- [ ] **Story 4.3: Implement Desktop "Top Menu" Navigation Experience**
  - [ ] Create conditional rendering for AppBar central area:
    - [ ] Render in AppBar central area if menuPosition === TOP and viewport ≥768px
    - [ ] Replace simpler Epic 3 top menu navigation
  - [ ] Implement normal state display with opacity/underline indicators:
    - [ ] Display current selected group name
    - [ ] Show horizontal row of URL items for current group only
    - [ ] Display favicons (or fallback) and effective titles
    - [ ] Visual states: opacity 0.5 (unloaded), 1.0 (loaded), blue underline (active)
  - [ ] Add hover-to-expand interaction:
    - [ ] Hovering triggers expanded view below AppBar central area (using MUI Popper/div)
    - [ ] Expanded view shows current group + URLs and other groups + URLs with visual states
    - [ ] Mouse-out collapses view smoothly with suitable delay
  - [ ] Create expanded view interaction handling:
    - [ ] Clicking URL calls setActiveUrl(), updates selected group state, collapses expansion
  - [ ] Implement responsive adaptation for tablets (768px - 1199px):
    - [ ] Horizontal URL rows have condensed spacing
    - [ ] Overflowing URL rows become horizontally scrollable (touch-swipe)
    - [ ] Add "More" (•••) icon that opens MUI Menu with overflowed URL items
  - [ ] Ensure proper layout and scrolling:
    - [ ] Fit within AppBar/popper
    - [ ] No main page scroll
    - [ ] Application maintains 100% viewport height
  - [ ] Optimize for smooth animations (300ms) and efficient rendering (memoization)
  - Success criteria: Rich, intuitive "Top Menu" experience with visual indicators
  - Dependencies: Stories 3.8, 4.1, 4.2

