    - [ ] Click group header to expand/collapse
    - [ ] Click URL to set active URL
    - [ ] Visual states: opacity 0.5 (unloaded), 1.0 (loaded), blue right side border (active)
  - [ ] Ensure proper integration with IframeManager:
    - [ ] Consume useIframeManager and group/URL data
    - [ ] Update active URL and selected group state
  - [ ] Add smooth animations and transitions:
    - [ ] 300ms animations for panel/accordion transitions
    - [ ] Efficient rendering with appropriate optimizations
  - Success criteria: Rich, organized "Side Menu" experience with visual indicators
  - Dependencies: Stories 4.1, 4.2

- [ ] **Story 4.5: Implement Click and Long-Press for URLs**
  - [ ] Create single-click behavior for all menus:
    - [ ] If URL not active OR unloaded: setActiveUrl() (loads via src from data-src)
    - [ ] If URL active AND loaded: Reload active iframe content
    - [ ] Update menu item to "active" state (opacity 1.0 + indicator)
    - [ ] Clear "Content Unloaded" message if visible
  - [ ] Implement long-press detection with visual feedback:
    - [ ] Create hook/logic to detect 2s sustained press with 0.3s delay before animation
    - [ ] Add visual progress bar (orange, 2-3px thick, bottom edge of item)
    - [ ] Include optional tooltip ("Hold for 2s to unload")
    - [ ] Manage event listeners properly
  - [ ] Add unload action for long-press:
    - [ ] On 2s press: markUrlAsUnloaded() (sets iframe src="", state "loaded: false")
    - [ ] Update menu item to "unloaded" state (opacity 0.5, loses active indicator)
    - [ ] Add haptic feedback on mobile devices
  - [ ] Create UI for unloaded active URLs:
    - [ ] Hide unloaded URL's iframe (visibility: hidden)
    - [ ] Display centered "Content Unloaded" text
    - [ ] Add "Reload Content" MUI Button (variant="outlined" with refresh icon)
    - [ ] Set background to match current theme
  - [ ] Implement cancellation of long-press:
    - [ ] Release before 2s or move pointer away cancels long-press
    - [ ] Reset progress indicator
    - [ ] Ensure no single-click triggered on cancellation
  - [ ] Ensure proper integration with IframeManager:
    - [ ] Actions update useIframeManager states
    - [ ] Menu indicators update instantly
  - Success criteria: Intuitive URL interactions with visual feedback
  - Dependencies: Story 4.2

- [ ] **Story 4.6: Ensure Advanced Features Work in Mobile Drawer**
  - [ ] Implement visual states for mobile drawer URL items:
    - [ ] Opacity 0.5 (unloaded), 1.0 (loaded)
    - [ ] Active URL has blue right side border
  - [ ] Add click interaction in mobile context:
    - [ ] Single-click triggers "Activate/Ensure Loaded/Reload"
    - [ ] Update iframe, close drawer, update indicators
  - [ ] Create long-press interaction with haptic feedback:
    - [ ] Long-press (2s) triggers "Unload URL Content"
    - [ ] Show visual progress bar on item's bottom edge
    - [ ] Add haptic feedback on successful long-press
    - [ ] Update item to "unloaded" state (opacity 0.5)
    - [ ] Show "Content Unloaded" UI in iframe area
  - [ ] Ensure mobile usability and touch optimization:
    - [ ] Provide adequate touch targets
    - [ ] Ensure smooth animations on mobile devices
    - [ ] Remember drawer state (expanded group) during session
  - [ ] Maintain consistency with desktop experiences:
    - [ ] State changes via useIframeManager consistent across platforms
    - [ ] "Loaded"/"unloaded" status universal across all views
  - Success criteria: Consistent, rich mobile experience for URL interactions
  - Dependencies: Stories 4.2, 4.5

## Affected Components

- User settings schema and APIs
- React contexts and custom hooks
- Dashboard layout and navigation components
- Iframe management system
- Interaction handlers (click, long-press)
- Mobile-specific components

## Dependencies

- Epic 1 (User Schema, Authentication)
- Epic 2 (User Profile Management)
- Epic 3 (Basic Iframe Display, Header)
- Material UI v6
- React Context API

## Technical Considerations

- Iframe state preservation requires careful implementation using CSS visibility and positioning
- Long-press detection needs debounce and animation synchronization (with 0.3s delay before animation)
- Visual indicators must update instantly on state changes
- Theme application must support system preference detection via `prefers-color-scheme` media query
- Mobile touch interactions need proper event handling with haptic feedback
- Performance optimization through memoization and efficient React Context usage
- Responsive design considerations for different viewport sizes (desktop vs. tablet vs. mobile)

